// This is your Prisma schema file,
// learn more about it in the docs: https://pris.ly/d/prisma-schema

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

model User {
  id               String                  @id @default(uuid())
  email            String                  @unique
  name             String
  contactNumber    String?                 @unique
  githubProfile    String?
  linkedinProfile  String?
  isActive         Boolean                 @default(true)
  role             Role
  gender           Gender
  specialization   Specialization?         @relation(fields: [specializationId], references: [id])
  semester         Int?
  enrollmentYear   Int?
  specializationId String?
  isAdmin          Boolean                 @default(false)
  College          College?                @relation(fields: [collegeId], references: [id])
  collegeId        String?
  Activities       ActivityLogs[]
  createdAt        DateTime                @default(now())
  quiz             QuizAssigendToStudent[]
  scores           StudenQuizScores[]
}

model Specialization {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  name      String
  User      User[]
  Quiz      Quiz[]
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  College   College? @relation(fields: [collegeId], references: [id])
  collegeId String?
}

model College {
  id              String           @id @default(uuid())
  name            String           @unique
  email           String           @unique
  contactNumber   String?          @unique
  address         String?
  logoSrc         String?
  directorName    String
  collegeWebsite  String?
  description     String?
  Users           User[]
  specializations Specialization[]
  quizes          Quiz[]
  createdAt       DateTime         @default(now())
}

model Quiz {
  id               String                  @id @default(uuid())
  name             String                  @unique
  duration         Int?
  description      String?
  isPublished      Boolean
  publishedAt      DateTime?
  Questions        QuizQuestions[]
  Specialization   Specialization          @relation(fields: [specializationId], references: [id])
  specializationId String
  createdById      String
  createdAt        DateTime                @default(now())
  College          College?                @relation(fields: [collegeId], references: [id])
  collegeId        String?
  user             QuizAssigendToStudent[]
  score            StudenQuizScores[]
}

model QuizQuestions {
  id        String                 @id @default(uuid())
  question  String
  type      QuizQuestionType
  Choices   QuizQuestionsChoices[]
  Quiz      Quiz?                  @relation(fields: [quizId], references: [id])
  quizId    String?
  createdAt DateTime               @default(now())
}

model QuizQuestionsChoices {
  id              String         @id @default(uuid())
  QuizQuestions   QuizQuestions? @relation(fields: [quizQuestionsId], references: [id])
  quizQuestionsId String?
  text            String
  isCorrect       Boolean
  createdAt       DateTime       @default(now())
}

model QuizAssigendToStudent {
  id         String   @id @default(uuid())
  User       User?    @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  userId     String?
  Quiz       Quiz?    @relation(fields: [quizId], references: [id])
  quizId     String?
  assignedAt DateTime @default(now())
  assignedBy String
}

model ActivityLogs {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  User      User?    @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  userId    String?
  activity  String
  type      String
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
}

model StudenQuizScores {
  id               String   @id @default(uuid())
  duration         Decimal
  score            Decimal
  isPassed         Boolean
  attemptedAt      DateTime
  correctCount     Int
  incorrectCount   Int
  unAttemptedCount Int
  User             User?    @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  userId           String?
  Quiz             Quiz?    @relation(fields: [quizId], references: [id])
  quizId           String?
}

enum QuizQuestionType {
  Single
  MCQ
}

enum Gender {
  Male
  Female
  other
}

enum Role {
  student
  faculty
  spoc
}

const express = require('express')
const router = express.Router()

const { Postgres } = require('../../db')

//get all the users
router.get('/', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const result = await Postgres.user.findMany({
      include: {
        College: {
          select: {
            name: true
          }
        },
        specialization: {
          select: {
            name: true
          }
        }
      }
    })
    if (result) {
      res
        .status(200)
        .json({ status: 200, msg: 'retrived successfully', result })
    }
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({
      status: 500,
      msg: error.toString() || 'something went wrong with the api server',
      result: null
    })
  }
})

//get a user
router.get('/:id', async (req, res) => {
  const { id } = req.params
  try {
    const result = await Postgres.user.findFirst({
      where: {
        id
      },
      include: {
        College: {
          select: {
            name: true
          }
        },
        specialization: {
          select: {
            name: true
          }
        }
      }
    })
    if (result) {
      res
        .status(200)
        .json({ status: 200, msg: 'retrived successfully', result })
    } else
      res
        .status(200)
        .json({ status: 404, msg: 'no user found with this ID', result: null })
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({
      status: 500,
      msg: error.toString() || 'something went wrong with the api server',
      result: null
    })
  }
})

// create a user
router.post('/', async (req, res) => {
  console.log('here we are')
})

// import users by excle
router.post('/', async (req, res) => {
  console.log('here we are')
})

module.exports = router








const express = require('express')
const router = express.Router()

const { Postgres } = require('../../db')

router.get('/', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const result = await Postgres.college.findMany()
    if (result) {
      res.status(200).json({
        status: 200,
        msg: 'retrived successfully',
        result
      })
    }
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({
      status: 500,
      msg: error.toString() || 'something went wrong with the api server',
      result: null
    })
  }
})

router.get('/:id', async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id
  try {
    const result = await Postgres.college.findFirst({
      where: {
        id
      },
      include: {
        Users: {
          include: {
            specialization: true
          }
        }
      }
    })
    if (result) {
      res
        .status(200)
        .json({ status: 200, msg: 'retrived successfully', result })
    } else
      res.status(200).json({
        status: 404,
        msg: 'no college found with this ID',
        result: null
      })
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({
      status: 500,
      msg: error.toString() || 'something went wrong with the api server',
      result: null
    })
  }
})

router.patch('/:id', async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id
  try {
    const result = await Postgres.college.update({
      where: {
        id
      },
      data: req.body
    })
    if (result) {
      res.status(200).json({ status: 200, msg: 'updated successfully', result })
    } else
      res.status(200).json({
        status: 404,
        msg: 'no college found with this ID',
        result: null
      })
  } catch (error) {
    console.log(error)
    res.status(500).json({
      status: 500,
      msg: error.toString() || 'something went wrong with the api server',
      result: null
    })
  }
})

module.exports = router
